Captive portal

NOTE: The IP address of the Ethernet interface is hardcoded to 192.168.0.14 in /etc/configuration/network. You need to change it if you would like to use another address.

Run
ndsctl status
to see the configuration and the authenticated clients.

Run
ndsctl deauth 192.168.0.12
to make the user with IP 192.168.0.12 authenticate again (can also use MAC address)

Start 
nodogsplash -f -d 7
to see verbose output
